      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I’m not following. There are 3 boards being moved. \n\u003e \n\u003e - 2 from IBM - these both have com.ibm identifiers (openpower). Assuming Matt can confirm these aren’t actually his boards. \n\nThe FP5280G3 platform is based on OpenPower. In OpenPower systems, the VPD structures typically use `com.ibm` identifiers, so the configuration keeps those identifiers to remain consistent with the existing OpenPower platform conventions.\n\n\u003e - 1 from Asrock - this has a FruDevice probe already but is just a model number and no board/product manufacturers.  Maybe we can get George to add those. \n\nFor the NF5280M7 configuration, I also added board manufacturer information.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e Would it be easier if these were two different commits?\n\nThanks for the feedback. 😊\n\nI have split the original change into two commits to make the changes clearer for review.",
